d optical potential\ninputs, within the framework of second order DWBA, taking into account\nsimultaneous, successive and non-orthogonality contributions provide, within\nexperimental errors an overall account of the experimental findings for all of\nthe measured (A+2)Sn(p,t)(A)Sn(gs) reactions, for which absolute cross sections\nhave been reported to date.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 18 Oct 2012 10:52:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-11"}
